creating instance with terraform:
 
 
create an ec2 instance
connect in terminal
 
sudo yum install -y yum-utils shadow-utils
 
sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://rpm.releases.hashicorp.com/AmazonLinux/hashicorp.repo
 
sudo yum -y install terraform
 
mkdir /rnk
cd /rnk
 
 
goto aws
goto iam
create a user
attach policy -> administrator access
get keys ->access and secret key
vim provider.tf
 
This has to be pasted after vim command
********************************************************************
provider "aws" {
  region     = "us-east-1"
  access_key = "paste the created key"
  secret_key = "8avLzHFz78+wa0WpFYZW0rIdEzsHHEkHeVsjyjUr"
}
 
resource "aws_instance" "my-server" {
  ami           = "ami-00ca32bbc84273381"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
  tags = {
    Name = "india-server"
  }
}
*******************************************************************
inside vim:
 
ami-00ca32bbc84273381
esc : w q ! enter
 
terraform init
 
yum install tree -y
tree -a
terraform validate
terraform fmt
terraform plan
terraform apply
 
goto ec2 
refresh
new instance created successfully
 
 
select the new instace created
select tags below
manage tags
under value -> change the name to anything
save
 
goto terminal
terraform plan 
terraform apply // the change is showed
 
output= one chnaged
